ELIZABETH TAYLOR

British-American actress

Born February 27, 1932, London, England

Died March 23, 2011

Elizabeth Taylor won Oscars for BUtterfield 8 and Who's Afraid of Virginia Woolf? and nominations for Raintree County, Cat On a Hot Tin Roof and Suddenly, Last Summer. She was in National Velve, Life With Father, Little Women, Father of the Bride, A Place In the Sun, Giant, The V.I.P.'s, and Cleopatra.

THALIA

Mexican singer and actress

Born August 26, 1971, Mexico City, Mexico

As a vocalist, Thalía had major hits with such songs as "Entre el mar y una estrella", "Tú y Yo", "No me enseñaste", and "Closer To You". She is also a very popular star of telenovelas.

TIFFANI THIESSEN

American actress

Born January 23, 1974, Long Beach, California

Tiffani Thiessen is best known for playing Kelly Kapowski on the TV series Saved By the Bell, as well as Valerie Malone in Beverly Hills 90210 and Elizabeth Burke in White Collar.

LEA THOMPSON

American actress

Born May 31, 1961, Rochester, Minnesota

Lea Thompson starred as Caroline Duffy in the sitcom Caroline In the City, and was in the Back To the Future trilogy as well as All the Right Moves, Some Kind of Wonderful, The Beverly Hillbillies, and TV series Switched At Birth.

COURTNEY THORNE-SMITH

American actress

Born November 8, 1967, San Francisco, California

Courtney Thorne-Smith is known for her television roles on Melrose Place, Ally McBeal, According To Jim, and Two and a Half Men.

UMA THURMAN

American actress

Born April 29, 1970, Boston, Massachusetts

Uma Thurman has starred in such movies as Pulp Fiction, Gattaca, the Kill Bill films, The Producers, and Percy Jackson and the Olympians: The Lightning Thief.

CHERYL TIEGS

American model

Born September 25, 1947, Breckenridge, Minnesota

Cheryl Tiegs is a supermodel, at the height of her popularity in the late 1970's.

GENE TIERNEY

American actress

Born November 19, 1920, Brooklyn, New York

Died November 6, 1991

Gene Tierney starred in the movies Tobacco Road, Heaven Can Wait, Laura, Leave Her To Heaven (for which she received an Oscar nomination), The Razor's Edge, The Ghost and Mrs. Muir, The Mating Season and The Left Hand of God.

JENNIFER TILLY

American actress

Born September 16, 1958, Los Angeles, California

Jennifer Tilly was in the movies Johnny Be Good, The Fabulous Baker Boys, Bullets Over Broadway, Made In America, Liar Liar, and Bride of Chucky.

CHARLENE TILTON

American actress

Born December 1, 1958, San Diego, California

Charlene Tilton is best known in the role of Lucy Ewing in the TV series Dallas.

ASHLEY TISDALE

American actress and singer

Born July 2, 1985, Monmouth County, New Jersey

Ashley Tisdale got her start as a Disney diva, in the TV series The Suite Life of Zack and Cody and the High School Musical films. She was in the TV shows Hellcats and Carol's Second Act.

MARISA TOMEI

American actress

Born December 4, 1964, Brooklyn, New York

Marisa Tomei has starred in the movies My Cousin Vinny, Chaplin, Slums of Beverly Hills, In the Bedroom, Anger Management, Crazy Stupid Love, and The Rewrite.

MICHELLE TRACHTENBERG

American actress

Born October 11, 1985, New York, New York

Michelle Trachtenberg played Dawn Summers in the TV series Buffy the Vampire Slayer and Georgina Sparks in Gossip Girl. She was in the movies Inspector Gadget, EuroTrip, Ice Princess and 17 Again.

KATHLEEN TURNER

American actress

Born June 19, 1954, Springfield, Missouri

Kathleen Turner was in the movies Body Heat, Romancing the Stone, Prizzi's Honor, Peggy Sue Got Married, The Accidental Tourist, and The Virgin Suicides.

LANA TURNER

American actress

Born February 8, 1921, Wallace, Idaho

Died June 29, 1995

Lana Turner was in Love Finds Andy Hardy, Dr. Jekyll and Mr. Hyde, Johnny Eager, The Postman Always Rings Twice, The Three Musketeers, The Merry Widow, The Bad and the Beautiful, Peyton Place, Imitation of Life, and Madame X.

TINA TURNER

American singer

Born November 26, 1939, Nutbush, Tennessee

Died May 24, 2023

Tina Turner sang the hit songs "River Deep - Mountain High" and "Proud Mary" (with Ike & Tina Turner) and solo hits "What's Love Got To Do With It", "Better Be Good To Me", "We Don't Need Another Hero", "Typical Male", and "The Best".

SHANIA TWAIN

Canadian singer

Born Auguts 28, 1965, Windsor, Ontario, Canada

Country singer Shania Twain has recorded such hits as "Any Man of Mine", "No One Needs To Know", "From This Moment On", "That Don't Impress Me Much" and "Come On Over".

SHANNON TWEED

Canadian model and actress

Born March 10, 1957, St. John's, Newfoundland, Canada

Shannon Tweed was Playboy's Playmate of the Year for 1982 and starred in a string of "B" movies in the 1980's and 90's.
